properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 2:41PM CST until January 14 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 6
AM CST TUESDAY...

.Snow is expected to develop over eastern Minnesota this evening
and work into west central Wisconsin overnight. Accumulations from
2 to 4 inches are expected to occur, mainly before midnight. The
heavier accumulation will likely occur along the I-94 corridor,
and along and east of Highway 53.

The accumulating snow should end after midnight to the east, but
some patchy freezing drizzle could remain for a time after the
snow ends.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4
inches.

* WHERE...Portions of northwest and west central Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Heavier snow totals are expected along the
I-94 corridor. Heaviest accumulations expected to occur from 8
PM until Midnight.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
